translated: Engström, Helge Fredrik, bank director, Vetlanda, born on October 8th, 1894 in Växjö as the son of real estate owner Nils E. and Hanna Jonsson. Married on February 22nd to Elisabeth Wingren. Completed secondary education in 1912 and underwent practical training in business. Employed at Skandia Banken in 1912 and at A-B Skånska Banken in 1913, acting cashier in Växjö in 1917, first cashier in Kristianstad in 1919, cashier at the main office in 1928, accountant in Vetlanda in 1931, and director since 1937. Member of the city council since 1935, on the board of A-B Vetlanda Stadshotell and Vetlanda conservative party, approved auditing officer for the chamber of commerce in Småland and Blekinge, and vice chairman of the Freemason brotherhood Njudung.
